1. Scatter / Bubble Chart with Multiple Dimensions in Rows


Tableau Capability

Tableau supports multiple dimensions on Rows, allowing detailed segmentation of scatter and bubble charts while maintaining size, color, and shape encodings.

 

2.Marker + Area / Line Combination Charts


Tableau Capability

Tableau allows layering different mark types (markers, areas, lines) within a single view, providing highly flexible storytelling visuals.

 

3.Dynamic Measure Switching Based on Parameters


Tableau Capability

Tableau parameters can dynamically control which measure is displayed across visuals without complex calculations.

 

4.Running Total in Marimekko / Advanced Bar Charts


Tableau Capability

Tableau supports Marimekko charts with running totals, allowing analysis of both contribution and trend simultaneously.

 

5.100% Stacked Bar Chart with Absolute Value Line


Tableau Capability

Tableau allows combining normalized (100%) stacked bars with an overlaying line that shows absolute totals in the same chart, enabling relative and absolute analysis simultaneously.

 

6.Gantt Chart with Dynamic Legends


Tableau Capability

Tableau natively supports Gantt charts with flexible legend behavior, where legends can dynamically change based on parameter selection. It also supports multiple dimensions on the axis, enabling complex scheduling and dependency analysis.
